 ."]},{"name":"Lattimer","meanings":["English: variant of   Latimer  ."]},{"name":"Lattner","meanings":["English: variant of   Latimer  .","German: occupational name for a carpenter who prepared or used laths or slats, from Middle High German <i>latte</i> ‘slat, lath’ + <i>-n</i> (plural suffix) + the agent suffix <i>-er</i>."]}]},{"name":"Margery","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual medieval vernacular form of   Margaret   (now also commonly spelled   Marjorie  ). This form of the name is preserved in the nursery rhyme ‘See-saw, Margery Daw’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":12,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Margery Latimer was born about 1443, in Dorset, England, her father, Sir Nicholas Latymer, was 12 and her mother, Joanna Hody, was 14. She married Richard Hals in 1464, in Devon, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She died in 1500, in Sherford, Devon, England, at the age of 58."},"et":{"about 1443–1500":"umbes 1443–1500","1443–1464":"1443–1464","1443–1500":"1443–1500","1450–1504":"1450–1504","1439–1488":"1439–1488","1465–Male":"1465–Surnud","1471–1559":"1471–1559","1472–1559":"1472–1559","1432–1505":"1432–1505","1430–1504":"1430–1504","1472":"1472","1450":"1450","1471":"1471","1500":"1500","1455":"1455","1488":"1488","1465":"1465","1432":"1432","1443":"1443","1464":"1464","1430":"1430","21 June 1488":"21. juuni 1488","about 1443":"umbes 1443",